'''Lucas Marangon''' is primarily known as the artist of the ''Tag & Bink'' comic stories, written by [[Kevin Rubio]] for [[Dark Horse Comics]], and has illustrated other short pieces, mostly humor-related, in ''[[Star Wars Tales]]'', including "[[Marooned]]," for which he also wrote the script. He was also the cover colorist for the ''[[Star Wars: General Grievous]]'' series, and the penciller and cover artist for ''[[Star Wars: Qui-Gon and Obi-Wan: The Aurorient Express]]''. Currently, he works as the official ''Star Wars'' illustrator for [[The Walt Disney Company|Disney]] LATAM.

